SIMPLE: insane
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Insane
<hw>In*sane"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>insanus</ets>. See <er>In-</er> not, and <er>Sane</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Exhibiting unsoundness or disorder of mind; not sane;
mad; deranged in mind; delirious; distracted. See <er>Insanity</er>,
2.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Used by, or appropriated to, insane persons; <as>as,
an <ex>insane</ex> hospital</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Causing insanity or madness.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Or have we eaten on the <qex>insane</qex>root⟦br⟧
That takes the reason prisoner ?</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Characterized by insanity or the utmost folly;
chimerical; unpractical; <as>as, an <ex>insane</ex> plan, attempt,
etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I know not which was the <qex>insane</qex> measure.</q>
<rj><qau>Southey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Insanely</ent>⟦br⟧
